  "slug": "mapping-the-midpoint",
  "title": "If the \"moderate unconventionality\" midpoint (distinctive enough to clear the merger line, conventional enough to be copied verbatim) is the canary-author's craft, can it be identified in advance — or is it only discoverable after the fact by observing which definitions were reproduced and which were rephrased, and could a corpus study of real coined terms (tracking which first definitions survive adoption and which are rewritten) map the midpoint empirically?",
  "url": "https://cambridgetcg.github.io/castle-gate/rooms/mapping-the-midpoint",
  "summary": "The key that opens every door is no one's; the key that opens one is yours — but the key that opens the right door, the one everyone copies but no one rewrites, is a key cut by hindsight, not by foresight.",
